      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>The Christianburg Industrial Alumni Association was formed
         in 1976. At this time a social organization was formed and
         they called themselves the "Christianburg Institute Alumni
         Association". The officers were David Hickman,President,Amanda
         DeHart,Vice President,Charles Johnson,Director of
         Affairs,Mattie P. Holmes,Recording Secretary,and Carrie
         Price,Treasurer.</p>
         <p>Several committees were formed and the purpose of the
         organization was established. Through the succeeding years a
         number of meetings were held,a scholarship fund was
         established and in 1986 a commerative monument was erected on
         the site. Additional material about Christianburg may be found
         in the: John Banks Papers Acc.# 1984-34,The Amanda DeHart
         Papers Acc.# 1988-61, The Colson-Hill Family Papers Acc.#
         1965-13, The VTA Papers Acc.#1969-14, and the VIA Papers ACC.#
         1969-37 all may be found in the Virginia State University
         Special Collections Archives.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>These materials document the negative impact of school
         integration in Virginia. Throughout Virginia and south.
         Institutions that had been established,built and nurtured by
         the African American Community were by routine closed or down
         graded. The records of Christianburg and other schools for
         Frican American, thier accomplishments and failures help to
         document and define the reality of what was unequal and
         seperate.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement>
         <head>Series Description</head>
         <p>Series I. CIAA Letters Copies of the papers of Edgar A.
         Long 1966-1986</p>
         <p>Series II. Photographs Class scenes 1948-1950 and 1962</p>
         <p>Series III. Memorabilia Autograph book from the class of
         1935</p>
         <p>Series IV. Printed Programs: The Schaeffer Memorial Baptist
         Church</p>
         <p>Series V. Scrapbook Titled the Second Collectable Book,
         Photographs, and News Clippings of school scenes and meetings
         of the Christianburg Alumni Association.</p>
         <p>Series VI. Christianburg Artifacts Three dimentional items
         associated with the history of Christianburg Industrial
         Institute.</p>
      </arrangement>
